    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                <date>6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Feby 1850</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Is Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I am about to presume on<lb/> an old acquaintanceship—trust you will
                not think<lb/> me troublesome.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I have been as you will see, elected<lb/> Jnos &amp; <add>?</add> to
                their society &amp; have accepted much<lb/> against my inclination you will more or
                less be<lb/> as quick at guessing why—as I could write—the first<lb/> name
                    <del>of</del> in the list <del>will explain</del> of officers
                    <sic>comprizing</sic><lb/> the Board, will explain all—as I have however<lb/>
                been reduced by <add>?</add> friends who along with me<lb/> evince much interest in
                every particular con<lb/>nected<add>?</add> unto our holy religion, to accept
                office<lb/> for the success of this society. I have done so<lb/> enclosed I send you
                a communication to the<lb/> effect of the society being organized with a
                request<lb/> that you will publish <add>?</add> in the occident<lb/> do me the favor
                to correct the style of this<lb/> communication should there be any fault—prior<lb/>
                to inserting it—I trust my dear Sir you will<lb/> not permit the publication of this
                uncorrected—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I recd a letter from <persName>Jacob</persName> yesterday<lb/> who
                wrote me that he would leave your city<lb/> for <placeName>New York</placeName> the
                following week. Should he not have<lb/> done so oblige me in handing him the
                enclosed letter</p>
            <p>over</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>You are no doubt acquainted with all the movements<lb/> of the Hebrew Portuguese
                congregation of the city &amp; must<lb/> therefore be aware <del>by</del> of
                    <persName>Mr Nathan's</persName> being engaged<lb/> as minister at a salary of
                2500$ per ann. The Syn<add>?</add><lb/> will not be consecrated until his return
                from <placeName>Jamaica</placeName><lb/> which will not probably be prior to
                    <date>Pentecost</date><lb/> Holidays.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I shall be happy to pay postage on<lb/> letters from you &amp; ask
                as a particular favor that<lb/> you acknowledge as soon as possible the receipt of
                this—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With kind regards from <persName>Miriam</persName> I<lb/> remain dr
                Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <sic>Respectfuly</sic>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Your obe Ser.</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">Daniel Wolff</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="Addressed to:"><addressee>Revd Isc Leeser</addressee>,
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
        </body>
